# Component Patterns

## HOOK-ENFORCED (will be blocked)
- NEVER use class components (`class X extends Component`). Use function components only.
- Every component SHOULD have an explicit Props interface (warned if missing).

## INSTRUCTION RULES
- NEVER prop drill. Children pull their own state from Jotai atoms. Pages are layout shells that compose feature components — they do NOT pass data down to children.
- Prefer composition. Build complex UI by composing smaller components, not by adding props.
- Error boundaries are REQUIRED on every route/page-level component.
- Use modular, composable code. Break logic into sensibly named hooks and components. A 50-line component doing one thing is better than a 200-line component doing three things.
